der funding strategy:\n* **Massive Capital Needs & Long Horizon:** The AI segment requires "significant capital expenditures" for compute infrastructure, power generation, and model training. The company expects a "multi-year investment horizon" before the AI segment translates into sustained positive Adjusted EBITDA.\n* **Public Market Financing:** To fund the aggressive scale-up required to capture a "$26.5 trillion potential market opportunity," the company explicitly states its plan to **"access a range of debt and equity financing solutions available to us as a public company"** rather than relying solely on internal cash flows from Connectivity. \n\nIn summary, while Connectivity is a massive cash and profit generator that fits into the company\'s historical model of using mature segments to fund nascent ones, the sheer capital intensity of the AI segment means the company plans to heavily utilize public debt and equity markets to fund its AI infrastructure build-out.',
